{0 Code action: create unresolved note}

For an unresolved ordinary-link diagnostic from {!page-"feature-diagnostics"},
provide a quick fix that creates the missing Markdown note.

{1 Activation}

The server advertises [codeActionProvider] for [quickfix]. A
[textDocument/codeAction] request returns the action when its range intersects
an unresolved ordinary wikilink or Markdown link with no fragment.

Broken embeds and images do not offer this action.

{1 Target path}

The link target is interpreted as a vault-relative path, matching
{!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve}. A missing [.md] suffix is appended. The
action is unavailable for absolute paths, path components [.] or [..], empty
components, or extensions other than [.md].

{1 Workspace edit}

The preferred quick fix is titled [Create note "path.md"]. Its workspace edit:

{ol
  {- creates the target without overwriting an existing file;}
  {- inserts an H1 using the target basename.}
}

The link source is unchanged because it already names the newly-created note.

{1 Limitations}

Fragment links are excluded because creating a file alone would not create the
requested heading or anchor. The action does not create parent directories.
